# Fault (two, on purpose): a side door declared ~400 mm off its host wall, plus a chest
#   blocking the entrance door's landing.
# Raises: W_DOOR_OFF_WALL (the side door) and W_DOORWAY_BLOCKED (the entrance).
# Heals with: arch fix THEN arch repair — fix attaches the off-wall door (a span edit,
#   ADR 0011), then repair clears the chest (a geometric move, ADR 0006). Exercises the
#   fix->repair ordering and that a second pass through the pipeline is a byte no-op.
plan "Combined Faults" {
  units mm
  grid 50
  wall id=w_ext exterior thickness 200 { (0,0) (6000,0) (6000,5000) (0,5000) close }
  room id=r at (0,0) size 6000x5000 label "R"
  door id=d_main at (1000,5000) width 900 wall exterior hinge left swing in
  door id=d_side at (6400,2500) width 900 wall exterior hinge left swing in
  window at (3000,0) width 1200 wall exterior
  furniture chest at (700,4400) size 800x500
}
